# UI Components and Styling

This project uses Gluestack UI components with NativeWind (Tailwind CSS) for styling.

## Component Imports

```tsx
// Gluestack UI components
import { Button, ButtonText } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { GluestackUIProvider } from "@/components/ui/gluestack-ui-provider";

// React Native components
import { View, Text } from "react-native";
```

## Styling with NativeWind

```tsx
// Use className for Tailwind styles
<View className="flex-1 justify-center items-center">
  <Text className="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">
    Hello World
  </Text>
</View>

// Or use style prop for React Native styles
<View style={{ flex: 1, justifyContent: 'center', alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <Text>Hello World</Text>
</View>
```

## Component Structure

- **`components/ui/`** - Gluestack UI components (buttons, providers, etc.)
- **`components/`** - Custom app-specific components
- Use Gluestack components for consistent design system
- Extend with custom components as needed

## Styling Guidelines

- Prefer NativeWind classes for layout and spacing
- Use React Native style prop for complex animations or platform-specific styles
- Follow the existing design patterns in the project
- Use semantic class names (e.g., `text-primary`, `bg-background`)
